SUMMARY:Talking About Abolition\, with Sonali Kolhatkar
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T120000
DTSTAMP:20260326T151215Z
UID:20260416T173000Z-17130@calendar.santarosa.edu
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T103000
ATTACH:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/live/image/gid/3/width/80/height/80/
 crop/1/src_region/0,0,384,384/581_calendar_square_-_Sonali_Kolhatkar.rev.1
 774562219.png
CATEGORIES:Department Events
DESCRIPTION:This talk will delve into how\, in a time of increased policin
 g\, immigration crackdowns\, and rising inequality\, an abolitionist under
 standing of the world can help us realize an economy built on the funding 
 of public goods rather than harsh enforcement.  Award winning journalist\,
  broadcaster\, writer\, and author\, Sonali Kolhatkar is the founder\, hos
 t\, and executive producer of Rising Up With Sonali which airs as a radio 
 program on KPFK\, KPFA\, and dozens of community radio stations around the
  U.S. and as a TV show on Free Speech TV\, and a podcast on Spotify and iT
 unes.  Sonali's book "Talking About Abolition: A Police-Free World is Poss
 ible" will be on sale by Reader's Books bookstore. Free food will also be 
 provided. This is a public event and is open to the community. This event 
 is part of Abolition April and Asian American Pacific Islander Heritage Mo
 nth.Visit SRJC's Intercultural Center website here! (https://intercultural
 .santarosa.edu/events)
LAST-MODIFIED:20260409T221547Z
LOCATION:Bertolini Student Activities Center - Santa Rosa Campus
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/17130-talking-about-abolition-wit
 h-sonali-kolhatkar
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  This talk will delve into how\, in a tim
 e of increased policing\, immigration crackdowns\, and rising inequality\,
  an abolitionist understanding of the world can help us realize an economy
  built on the funding of public goods rather than harsh enforcement.</p><p
 >  Award winning journalist\, broadcaster\, writer\, and author\, Sonali K
 olhatkar is the founder\, host\, and executive producer of Rising Up With 
 Sonali which airs as a radio program on KPFK\, KPFA\, and dozens of commun
 ity radio stations around the U.S. and as a TV show on Free Speech TV\, an
 d a podcast on Spotify and iTunes.</p><p>  Sonali's book "Talking About Ab
 olition: A Police-Free World is Possible" will be on sale by Reader's Book
 s bookstore. Free food will also be provided. This is a public event and i
 s open to the community. This event is part of Abolition April and Asian A
 merican Pacific Islander Heritage Month.</p><p><a href="https://intercultu
 ral.santarosa.edu/events" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit SRJC's Inte
 rcultural Center website here!</a></p>
