SUMMARY:The Sleep Lab: Building Better Habits for Sleep
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T180000
DTSTAMP:20260410T151320Z
UID:20260416T230000Z-17769@calendar.santarosa.edu
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T160000
ATTACH:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/live/image/gid/3/width/80/height/80/
 crop/1/src_region/0,0,2345,2345/591_CS_-_Lindley_STEM_2024_08_JS_015.rev.1
 775859111.jpg
CATEGORIES:Department Events
DESCRIPTION:Student Health PEERs are excited to host an engaging and inter
 active workshop focused on building better sleep habits to support student
 s' overall well-being and daily performance.  Workshop Details:Guest Speak
 er: Megan Blocker is a therapist trainee at SRJC Student Psychological Ser
 vices and a doctoral candidate at the PAU-Stanford PsyD Consortium. She is
  currently involved in the Computational Psychiatry\, Neuroimaging\, and S
 leep Lab (CoPsyN) at Stanford University School of Medicine\, where she is
  developing skills in assessing and treating sleep disorders.Peer-led acti
 vities: Peers will lead hands-on activities including creating your own ar
 omatherapy remedies and sleep journals as practical strategies for improvi
 ng sleep quality.  Whether you're looking to feel more rested\, improve fo
 cus\, or simply learn more about healthy sleep practices\, this workshop o
 ffers valuable tools in a supportive and interactive environment.Visit the
  SHS website here! (https://shs.santarosa.edu/peers)
LAST-MODIFIED:20260410T221320Z
LOCATION:Lindley STEM Center\, Room 138 - Santa Rosa Campus
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/17769-the-sleep-lab-building-bett
 er-habits-for-sleep
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Student Health PEERs are excited to host
  an engaging and interactive workshop focused on building better sleep hab
 its to support students' overall well-being and daily performance.</p><p> 
  Workshop Details:<br /><br /><strong>Guest Speaker:</strong> Megan Blocke
 r is a therapist trainee at SRJC Student Psychological Services and a doct
 oral candidate at the PAU-Stanford PsyD Consortium. She is currently invol
 ved in the Computational Psychiatry\, Neuroimaging\, and Sleep Lab (CoPsyN
 ) at Stanford University School of Medicine\, where she is developing skil
 ls in assessing and treating sleep disorders.</p><p><strong>Peer-led activ
 ities:</strong> Peers will lead hands-on activities including creating you
 r own aromatherapy remedies and sleep journals as practical strategies for
  improving sleep quality.<br /><br />  Whether you're looking to feel more
  rested\, improve focus\, or simply learn more about healthy sleep practic
 es\, this workshop offers valuable tools in a supportive and interactive e
 nvironment.</p><p><a href="https://shs.santarosa.edu/peers" target="_blank
 " rel="noopener">Visit the SHS website here!</a></p>
