DESCRIPTION:The iconic annual Butter &amp\; Eggs Days Parade &amp\; Festiv
 al is back\, with its signature colorful floats\, marching bands\, elabora
 te chicken costumes\, and four city blocks of booths with crafts\, arts\, 
 live music\, food\, beverage gardens\, kids areas\, and more! This year’
 s theme is “America’s Birthday - Petaluma Style”—celebrating the n
 ation’s 250th while honoring Petaluma’s deep agricultural roots and se
 rious hometown spirit.&nbsp\; Quirky and zany\, we love being a part of it
 ! Stop by our booth to hear about the park’s latest developments\, enter
 tain the kiddos with nature art activities\, and generally hang out! The P
 etaluma River Park booth will be located in the "A Lot" on 4th/Kentucky St
 reet\, also known as the parking lot near the Petaluma Museum and Blue Zon
 es office. Look for a "Petaluma River Park" sign hanging under the canopy.
  Festival starts at 10 am\; parade starts at 12 pm. Want to volunteer with
  us that day?&nbsp\; Volunteers needed for booth set-up\, various tabling 
 and docent shifts throughout the day—including sharing new park developm
 ent updates and making fun nature crowns with the kids—plus the always a
 ppreciated pack-up crew. .fe-block-4e25abe0fa1ec151d800 {mix-blend-mode: \
