X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Sonoma County Go Wild Hikers": "https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-go-wild-hikers/events/314111977/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_sonoma_county_go_wild_hikers
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Go Wild Hikers
UID:event_314111977@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260411T025310Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T120000
SUMMARY:Helen Putnam Hike with dogs
DESCRIPTION:Go Wild Hikers\nTime for a South County hike. Helen Putnam Reg
 ional Park is a compact wilderness park featuring beautiful oak savanna\, 
 grasslands\, and ridges with panoramic views of the Petaluma Valley to the
  east and the Chileno Valley to the west.\n\n**Where We Meet**\nHelen Putn
 am Park **Chileno Valley parking lot**\n411 Chileno Valley Road\nPetaluma\
 , CA 94952\nGive yourself enough time to arrive\, use the restroom & pay p
 ark fee. It often takes longer than you think.\n\n**The Hike (Group Hike #
 340)**\nRidge\, Filaree\, Pomo\, Panorama and Savanna trails - a loop hike
 \nLength - +/-4.75 miles/+/-7.6 kilometers\nElevation change - +/-500 feet
 /+/-152 meters\nDifficulty - 5/10 - easy\nExposures - 70% sun / 30 % shade
  - poison oak\, ticks/insects and views.\nBring plenty of water. At least 
 34 oz./1 liter!\nDogs - Yes\, well behaved and on a leash.\nFacilities at 
 trail head - shade\, picnic tables and toilets\nCost - $5 cash.\nParking -
  $8 Sonoma County Regional Parks fee\, free with Regional Park pass or lim
 ited parking on Chileno Valley Rd.\nRemember to wear appropriate hiking sh
 oes\, bring plenty of water for your dog too\, a hat\, snack\, layered clo
 thing.\nPlease Do Not Use Any scented products the day of a group hike!\nO
 f course we will all look out for each other but ultimately\, hikers are r
 esponsible for their own safety and well-being during hikes.\n\n**After Hi
 ke Gathering?**\nStellina Pronto\nItalian cafe and bakery offering sweet a
 nd savory.\n23 Kentucky St\, Petaluma\, CA 94952\n[(707) 789-9556](https:/
 /www.google.com/search?q=bakery+in+petaluma&oq=bakery+in+petaluma&gs_lcrp=
 EgZjaHJvbWUyCQgAEEUYORiABDIHCAEQABiABDIICAIQABgWGB4yCAgDEAAYFhgeMggIBBAAGB
 YYHjIICAUQABgWGB4yCAgGEAAYFhgeMggIBxAAGBYYHjIICAgQABgWGB4yCAgJEAAYFhge0gEJ
 ODE2MWowajE1qAIIsAIB8QUAnE7ZNfLb6Q&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8#)\n[stellinapr
 onto.com](https://www.stellinapronto.com/_files/ugd/ec9596_6b3d35a3744947c
 eb383b4cd4deca1b7.pdf)\n\n**When We Meet**\nSunday April 19\, 2026\n9:00 a
 m - 12:00 pm\n**If your plans change after you sign up even if you're on t
 he waitlist\, please update your RSVP.**\nDo Not Attend if you are sick\, 
 running a fever\, were exposed to or have tested positive for Covid-19 or 
 Any other contagion!\nHike may be changed\, postponed or cancelled in case
  of excessive heat\, rain\, smoke/AQI\, illness\, zombie apocalypse etc...
  Check your email the night before for any possible changes.\n\n**Notice t
 o New Hikers Only**\n**"When a New Hiker (never hiked with me before) does
 n't show up (No Show) to their first hike with the group\, they will be re
 moved (not banned) from the group immediately."**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-go-wild-hikers/events/3
 14111977/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260403T220452Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260403T220452Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
