BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Petaluma River Park Foundation": "https://petalumariverpark.org/calendar/river-park-walk-ars2x-djslw-7jznw-6bahf-4ekgp-g342b"}
X-SOURCE-ID:petaluma_river_park
SUMMARY:FEET IN THE MUD- WORKSHOP 2
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260420T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260420T173000
UID:c902ba0e1973caa1f48e7c0d1d760461@petalumariverpark.org
DESCRIPTION:Reading Historical Newspaper Accounts of Chinese Expulsion\, 1
 850–1890: How Racism Is Naturalized and Taught Learn how racism is natur
 alized\, and explore the effects of such naturalization\, in this hands-on
  activity reading local newspapers on Chinese immigrants across the span o
 f 1850–1890. This lecture will be followed by a group discussion.&nbsp\;
  Limited seating. .fe-block-85475957e674f6699900 {mix-blend-mode: \; } Reg
 ister Here #block-a973df68af2696e0b05e {--sqs-block-content-flex: 0\; } #b
 lock-a973df68af2696e0b05e { --opacity: 100%\; --translate-x: 0px\; --trans
 late-y: 0px\; --rotation: 0deg\; --scale-x: 100%\; --scale-y: 100%\; --ske
 w-x: 0deg\; --skew-y: 0deg\; --origin-x: 50%\; --origin-y: 50%\; opacity: 
 var(--opacity\, 1)\; transform: translateX(var(--translate-x)) translateY(
 var(--translate-y)) rotate(var(--rotation)) scale(var(--scale-x)\, var(--s
 cale-y)) skewX(var(--skew-x)) skewY(var(--skew-y))\; transform-origin: var
 (--origin-x) var(--origin-y)\; } Image credit: Courtesy of Lina Hoshino\; 
 original images from Petaluma Argus-Courier .fe-block-3cef7ab56ae03de728ce
  {mix-blend-mode: \; } Petaluma River Park Foundation would like to thank 
 the State Coastal Conservancy (SCC) for the Coastal Stories grant allowing
  us to bring forward stories from communities and voices historically excl
 uded from the storytelling on California’s coast and publicly accessible
  lands. Our project will highlight three little-known or untold stories fr
 om the Coast Miwok\, Chinese\, and Latinx communities that helped shape th
 e place and culture of Petaluma and the River Park location.
LOCATION:Petaluma River Park Foundation\, 159 H Street\, Petaluma\, CA\, 9
 4952
URL:https://petalumariverpark.org/calendar/river-park-walk-ars2x-djslw-7jz
 nw-6bahf-4ekgp-g342b
X-SOURCE:Petaluma River Park
END:VEVENT
