 ader campus community!  Date: April 21st\, 2026  Time: 3:00–5:00 PM  Loc
 ation: SRJC Student Activity Center (SAC)  This 2-hour interactive session
  will explore the principles of Trauma-Informed Care and their application
  in professional environments. Participants will learn how to recognize an
 d respond to signs of burnout\, compassion fatigue\, and vicarious trauma 
 — and develop strategies to strengthen resilience and wellbeing.  This t
 raining is especially valuable for anyone in the helping professions or th
 ose looking to foster a more supportive\, trauma-informed workplace cultur
 e.  For more support\, visit SRJC's Human Services website. (https://human
 services.santarosa.edu/)
