DESCRIPTION:Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Center (DCC) and Queer Resou
 rce Center (QRC) for an afternoon of connection\, creativity\, and communi
 ty! Disabled &amp\; Queer Joy Night is a low-pressure mixer designed for d
 isabled and queer folks (and those who live at the intersection of both) t
 o come together\, relax\, and celebrate joy in all its forms.  Come hang o
 ut\, meet new people\, and enjoy:Snacks and refreshments  Chill crafts and
  creative activities  Games and casual fun  A welcoming\, affirming space 
 to just be    Whether you're looking to make new friends\, connect with co
 mmunity\, or simply unwind in a space that celebrates you—you belong her
 e.  April 29th  3:00–5:00 PM  SRJC Intercultural Center\, Pioneer Hall\,
  Room 380  This event is open to students\, staff\, community members\, an
 d anyone in between. Bring yourself\, bring a friend\, or come solo—ther
 e's space for you here.  For more information\, visit the DCC website here
 ! (https://drd.santarosa.edu/dcc)
LAST-MODIFIED:20260324T213139Z
