  (DCC) and Queer Resource Center (QRC) for an afternoon of connection\, cr
 eativity\, and community! Disabled &amp\; Queer Joy Night is a low-pressur
 e mixer designed for disabled and queer folks (and those who live at the i
 ntersection of both) to come together\, relax\, and celebrate joy in all i
 ts forms.</p><p>  Come hang out\, meet new people\, and enjoy:</p><ul><li>
 Snacks and refreshments  </li><li>Chill crafts and creative activities  </
 li><li>Games and casual fun  </li><li>A welcoming\, affirming space to jus
 t be  </li></ul><p>  Whether you're looking to make new friends\, connect 
 with community\, or simply unwind in a space that celebrates you—you bel
 ong here.</p><p>  April 29th<br />  3:00–5:00 PM<br />  SRJC Intercultur
 al Center\, Pioneer Hall\, Room 380</p><p>  This event is open to students
 \, staff\, community members\, and anyone in between. Bring yourself\, bri
 ng a friend\, or come solo—there's space for you here.</p><p>  For more 
 information\, <a href="https://drd.santarosa.edu/dcc" target="_blank" rel=
 "noopener">visit the DCC website here!</a></p>
