BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Pollyklaastheater": "https://www.pollyklaastheater.org/event/sandcastle-drama-camp-princess-the-pea-theme/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:pollyklaastheater
X-SOURCE:Polly Klaas Community Theater
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260608T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260612T150000
DTSTAMP:20260410T195334
CREATED:20260317T222142Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260317T223025Z
UID:10000270-1780909200-1781276400@www.pollyklaastheater.org
SUMMARY:SANDCASTLE DRAMA CAMP - Princess & The Pea Theme
DESCRIPTION:What: Kids explore the theater-making process through games and activities that build creativity\, collaboration\, and confidence. Each Sandcastle Drama Camp session explores a different story theme\, the campers re-write the script as an ensemble to incorporate all their *original creative ideas for story\, character\, and design* resulting in a completely unique final play for performance each week. \n\nDiscounts & Flexible Pricing (sliding scale) available to all. Please complete a form and we will confirm your discount code via email https://forms.gle/QixDYDky7VUUhy6b9\n\nWho: Kids ages 6-12 \n\nProgram led by Sandcastle Theater Company's professional teaching artists\nApprox. 16 students per weekly session (1:8 student/staff ratio)\n\nWhere: Polly Klaas Community Theater\, 417 Western Ave. Petaluma\, CA \nWhen: Monday – Friday\, 9am – 3pm \n\nJune 8 – 12 — make-your-own-play! Theme: The Princess & the Pea\nJuly 6 – 10 — make-your-own-play! Theme: Alice in Wonderland\nJuly 27 – 31 — make-your-own-play! Puss in Boots\n\nFinal Performances: Families and invited guests join us for a staged-reading/performance at 2:30pm on last day of the session. \nDaily Schedule: \n\n9am check-in/drop-off\n9:30am warm-up games\n10am session activities\n10:30am snack\n10:45am session activities\n12pm lunch\n12:30pm session activities\n1:30pm recess\n1:45pm session activities\n3pm check-out/pick-up\n\nNotes: \n\nKids bring their own lunch\, water bottle\, snacks
URL:https://www.pollyklaastheater.org/event/sandcastle-drama-camp-princess-the-pea-theme/
LOCATION:Polly Klaas Community Theater\, 417 Western Avenue\, Petaluma\, CA\, 94952\, United States
CATEGORIES:PKCT Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.pollyklaastheater.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/015541ec-1b94-4e44-90ac-3d5f7a2866b1.png
END:VEVENT
