DTSTART:20260628T020000Z
DTEND:20260628T050000Z
URL:https://tockify.com/pdaevents/detail/887/1782612000000
SUMMARY: Convergence Ecstatic Dance
DESCRIPTION:Join Us for Convergence Ecstatic Dance!\n\nConvergence is the
  Saturday night dance party you’ve been waiting for: the sultry vibe of l
 ow lights\, plenty of room on the dance floor to move\, no yelling to be 
 heard over the music\, no one spilling their drinks on the dance floor. T
 une in to the music\, your body\, your emotions\, the flow of the room\, 
 and let loose! This is your chance to connect with others and experience 
 the joy of ecstatic dance in a chill\, welcoming space. (There’s even a q
 uiet room for stretching and resting.) No experience needed – just bring 
 your energy and wear clothes you can move in. Don’t miss out on this fun\
 , in-person event where the music and your spirit come together!\n\nConve
 rgence is a conscious dance experience centering Queer & BIPOC folks and 
 welcoming allies. All ages\, ethnicities\, sexualities\, gender expressio
 ns\, and bodies welcome! No: alcohol\, drugs\, smoking\, shoes\, devices\
 , talking on the dance floor.\n\nConvergence is a spinoff from the origin
 al Ecstatic Dance electronic music. It has expanded to include music you 
 know and love as well as new music. It spans across musical genres includ
 ing hip hop\, reggaeton\, Afrobeats\, House\, and music from around the w
 orld that has a driving beat and makes your body move.\n\nLet the rhythm 
 show you how to move\, sing along or vocalize if the spirit moves you\, d
 ance alone or with a consenting partner. Use this as a sacred time to get
  in touch with your emotions\, release the ones that no longer serve you 
 and welcoming in joy\, levity\, play\, and peace.\n\n“Ecstatic Dance is a
  freeform movement journey\, held in a safe and sacred container\, & faci
 litated by a professional DJ. It’s a place where we can be our unique sel
 ves\, and also connected to a common source.” http://~ecstaticdance.org\n
 \nSo put on your comfy clothes\, come alone or grab a friend\, and get re
 ady to sweat it out! Experience the wonder of moving together silently in
  community and using body language to communicate. Come early to help cre
 ate the space and stay afterwards to talk to the friend you made on the d
 ancefloor and help clean up. Community is built by participating fully to
 gether\, and we’re excited to connect with you!
CATEGORIES:dance,LGBT,BIPOC,DJ
